{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"body":"END-TO-END PROOF COMPLETE (2026-07-10 21:04 UTC): forced re-review of merged change 492 emitted the first REAL production code_review artifact — ticket 8e68-601a-b32d-4302 (type code_review, title 'code-review: rebar~492 @ 40e42c962...', Decision PASS, change_fingerprint recorded), auto-linked relates_to e7f4 via the commit's rebar-ticket trailer, committed to the persistent worktree and auto-pushed to origin/tickets. Getting here required fixing a deeper defect than the missing PAT: a fresh entrypoint clone of the tickets branch is WRITE-DEAD (.env-id is gitignored -> 'ticket system not initialized'; container has no git identity -> commit fails), and emit_code_review_artifact swallows both silently — filed as bug d220-eeda-1909-4147 (discovered_from this ticket). Prod's persistent volume is now converged (ran rebar._store.ensures.run_ensures + set repo-local git identity RebarBotNava/joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com — both persist on the gerrit_reviewbot_tickets volume across restarts), but any fresh volume regresses until d220's entrypoint fix lands. AC1 is MET in prod. Remaining on this ticket: AC2 (autodeploy re-runs fetch-secrets before compose up so new env keys reach the box without a manual boot) — code work. Also recommended: swap the broad classic repo-scope PAT for a fine-grained contents:write-only token (human-mintable only)."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1783717851274835001,"uuid":"316a6486-d938-425d-9979-a2b588f0b250"}